description:
The APEX Digital Dashboard is HERE!  Thrilled to finally be able to share a product overview and demo some of the capabilities.   In its most basic form, this is an essential upgrade for the Q's.  In the right hands, it can completely transform your driving experience.

Get one for your Q50/Q60 here:
https://squarewheelsauto.com/products/apex-digital-dashboard-instrument-cluster-for-infiniti-q50-q60-2014-2024

Other models in the pipeline, sign up for launch announcement:
Infiniti G37: 
https://squarewheelsauto.com/products/apex-digital-dashboard-instrument-cluster-for-infiniti-g37-2008-2015

Nissan GT-R: 
https://squarewheelsauto.com/products/apex-digital-dashboard-instrument-cluster-for-nissan-gt-r

Check out the install guide (video coming soon):
https://squarewheelsauto.com/blogs/videos/apex-digital-cluster-installation-guide

Chapters: 
00:00 Intro - Fixing Infiniti's Miss (Again)
02:21 Overview & OEM Feature Support
04:19 Themes (current & more to come)
04:52 How to control the APEX Digital Dash
05:26 Demo: All menu screens
06:04 Easy Installation
06:58 Carplay Included
08:17 HDMI Input & MK7 = BEAST MODE
10:40 Do you need an MK7 for the APEX to work?
11:31 Pushing the limits (night vision?)
13:14 Outro! Blow up the comments!

comments.text:
an honest review over on the Q50 forums:

Pros:



 Enhanced Aesthetic: The digital dash provided a refreshed, modern look to the Q50.

 High-Quality Display: The display was sharp and visually appealing.

 OEM Functionality: All features functioned seamlessly with OEM systems.

 Ease of Installation: The installation process was straightforward and hassle-free.

 Instant Gear Change Display: Gear shifts were displayed immediately without delay.

 Easy Dash Updates: Updating the dash was simple and quick.

 Apple CarPlay Integration: Apple CarPlay was available directly on the dash.

 Responsive Support: Support was readily available and easy to contact.



Cons:



 Mileage Sync Issues: The mileage sync feature did not function correctly.

 RPM Gauge Lag: The RPM gauge experienced some lag during downshifts.

 Screen Burn-In: The screen developed burn-in after just three days of use.

 Lag in Themes 2 & 3: Themes 2 and 3 were noticeably slower compared to Theme 1.

During my brief time with the product, I experienced screen burn-in, which was a significant enough issue for me to opt for a return. Had I not faced this problem, I likely would have kept the unit, as the overall experience was more positive than negative. The return process was straightforward, and I received a full refund, for which I am grateful. I believe this product has potential and could improve with future updates. However, given my experience, I felt it was best to return the unit rather than wait for potential fixes.
